<font class="subhead"><center><u>Keynote Speeches</u></center></FONT><p>
<font class="subhead">Barrett Outlines the Future of the PC as the "Center of the Digital Universe"</font><br>
In his technology keynote that served as a precursor to the official kick-off of the 2001 International CES, Intel 
President and CEO Craig R. Barrett defined the role of the PC as the media center. Surrounded by a myriad of 
consumer electronics and accompanied by the popular Blue Man Group theatrical troupe, Mr. Barrett told the 
standing-room only crowd that the PC has evolved from a stand-alone device into the "central nervous system 
for the entertainment system of the home."  <br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="intel.doc">transcript</a> | <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7060&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |
<p></font>

<font class="subhead">Gates Opens 2001 International CES With Vision of "Extreme Entertainment"</b></font><br>
<font class="body">The 2001 International CES opened today with presentations defining the status of the consumer electronics 
industry in a networked world.  In the opening keynote address, Gary Shapiro, president and CEO of the 
Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), Congressman Darrell Issa (R-CA), chairman of CEA, and Bill Gates, 
chairman and chief software architect of Microsoft Corp., 
each outlined the importance of digital technology in the evolution of the consumer electronics industry.
 <br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.microsoft.com/billgates/speeches/2001/01-06ces.asp">transcript</a> | <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7063&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>
<font class="subhead">Palm CEO Carl Yankowski Stresses The Importance of Design and Makes First eWallet Purchase</b></font><br>
<font class="body">

Palm Inc. is a pioneer in the field of mobile and wireless Internet solutions for individuals, enterprises 
and educational institutions, and made history today with its mobile eWallet purchase.
 <br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="yankowski.doc">transcript</a> | <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7069&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>

<font class="subhead">CE Industry Is on the Cusp of a New Internet Revolution</font>
AOL President of Interactive Services Barry Schuler announced that the CE industry 
soon will embark on a new Internet revolution that will be driven by "consumers, 
convenience and convergence".  In his Executive Perspective address, Schuler urged 
the industry to listen to consumers as we enter the "age of transformation." 
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">|
<a href="/press/AOL KEYNOTE.doc">transcript</a> |<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7074&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | 
</font>
<p>
<hr noshade size="1"><p>



<font class="subhead">International CES Highlights Digital 
Technology</FONT><BR>
<font class="subhead2">World's Largest Technology 
Event Showcases the Products that Facilitate Consumers' Active 
Lives</FONT><BR>
More than 122,000 industry professionals from 120 countries 
came to Las Vegas this week to see the cutting edge in digital technology at the 
2001 International CES. The world's largest annual technology tradeshow, 
featuring 1.2 million net square feet of exhibit space, wrapped up today after 
four days of conference sessions, keynote speeches and exhibits of the latest 
developments in consumer electronics technology.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="closing release 2001.doc">full story</a> | </font>


<p>
<font class="subhead">Home Networking SuperSession Highlights<br> State-of-the-Industry</font></br>

A capacity crowd at the 2001 International CES flocked to yesterday's Home Networking Supersession, where 
experts candidly discussed the present and future home networking industry, including the role of Internet 
appliances, service issues, standards debates and "killer applications."
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7076&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | </font>
<p>
<font class="subhead">CE Industry Is on the Cusp of a New Internet Revolution</font></br>

AOL President of Interactive Services Barry Schuler announced that the CE industry 
soon will embark on a new Internet revolution that will be driven by "consumers, 
convenience and convergence".  In his Executive Perspective address, Schuler urged 
the industry to listen to consumers as we enter the "age of transformation." 
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7074&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | </font>


<p>

<font class="subhead">Wireless Experts At CES Look at How 3G Will Affect Consumers</font></br>

Industry leaders Kari-Pekka Wilska of Nokia, Philip Christopher of Audiovox Communications Corp. 
and Jon Thode of Motorola discuss the benefits that the next generation of wireless technology, 3G, 
will have on consumers.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7075&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">
full story</a> | </font>

<p>

<font class="subhead">Supersession at the 2001 International CES Asks "What Do Consumers Want?"</font></br>

Consumers want convenience, control and choice, as well as products that are digital, simple to use 
and inexpensive, said a panel of industry leaders at the "Outfitting the Digital Consumer" Supersession 
at the 2001 International CES.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7073&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press
">full story</a> | </font>


<p>

<font class="subhead">TechTV Announces Winners of "Best of CES"</font></br>

TechTV announced Hughes Network Systems - Satellite Return DirecPC as Best Workstyle winner and DataPlay Inc. - DataPlay Digital Media as Best Lifestyle winner at the 2001 International CES in Las Vegas, Nevada.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7072&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | </font>


<p>

<font class="subhead">Surround Music Makes Big Splash at CES</font><br>

Five-time Grammy jazz icon Herbie Hancock and Guitarist Peter Distefano of the bands Porno for Pyros and Venice Underground were the featured guests at the Surround Music Roundtable Supersession, treating attendees to a
 demonstration of the latest developments in surround music using samples from their own surround tracks.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7071&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | </font>
<p>

<font class="subhead">FCC Commissioner Powell Shares Regulatory Philosophy with CES Attendees</b></font><br>

<font class="body">In a special supersession yesterday at the 2001 International CES, Federal Communications 
Commissioner Michael Powell discussed the FCC and its involvement in many of the major issues facing the consumer 
electronics industry, including digital television, copyright protection and the retail availability of digital 
set-top boxes.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7068&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> | </font>
<p>

<font class="subhead">Digital Car Revolution Supersession Addresses the Future of Automotive Technology</b></font><br>

Four of the automotive industry's top executives, David Acton of General Motors/On Star, Patrick Lavelle of 
Audiovox Electronics, Jack Withrow of Diamler/Chrysler and Albert Wong of Clarion Advanced Technology Corp, 
discussed the impact of today's technologies on consumers' lives and the possible applications for the 
future.
 <br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7064&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>





<font class="subhead">Opening Remarks from CEA President<br> Gary Shapiro</font><br>
Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) President and CEO Gary Shapiro gave remarks prior to the 2001 CES Opening Keynote given by Bill Gates.  Shapiro's comments reflected on events of the past year in consumer electronics and looked ahead to the issues CEA plans to tackle in the comming year.
<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="garyshapiro.doc">transcript</a> |</font>
<p>

<font class="subhead">Innovations Awards at 2001 International CES Honor Best In Consumer Technology Design and Engineering</font><br>
The most widely renowned consumer technology awards program, Innovations recognizes the best designed and engineered 
products in 19 categories.  A true sense of imagination and excellence are evident in each of the Best of Showcase 
honorees.<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/awards/innovations_2001/?menuItem=4&subMenuItem=0&tabName=Attendee">link to award winners</a> | <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7062&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>


<font class="subhead">2000 Sales Exceed Expectations, 2001 Projections Are Strong</font><br>

Year-end 2000 sales of consumer electronics goods increased 10% from 1999 to $90.1 billion, 
and sales of consumer electronics goods from manufacturers to dealers will surpass $95.6 
billion in 2001, according to figures released by the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today.<br>
<font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7058&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>
<font class="subhead">CEA Honors New Consumer Electronics Hall of Fame Inductees at
2001 International CES</a><br></font>

Honoring the contributions of those leaders who have made a significant 
contribution to the consumer electronics industry and to build on the inaugural class of 2000, the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today announced seven new inductees into its Consumer Electronics Hall of Fame.
<br><font size="1" color="#999999">| 
<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7054&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
<p>



<font class="subhead">CEA Honors William Kasuga with Lifetime Achievement Award</font></br>

In recognition of his exceptional leadership and vision, the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today announced William Kasuga, co-founder and former chairman of the board for Kenwood U.S.A. Corp., winner of its Lifetime Achievement Award.
<font size="1" color="#999999">| <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/press/display_rel.asp?id=7055&menuItem=1&subMenuItem=1&tabName=Press">full story</a> |</font>
